<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78e34d9b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s1012a"><num value="1012a">§ 1012a.</num><heading> Funding</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to any other funds made available by this chapter, of the funds of the Commodity Credit Corporation, the Secretary shall make available to carry out this chapter $150,000,000 for fiscal year 2026 and each fiscal year thereafter, to remain available until expended.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78e34d9c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-04/ch656/s15">Aug. 4, 1954, ch. 656, § 15</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/115/334/tII/s2401/c">Pub. L. 115–334, title II, § 2401(c)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-20">Dec. 20, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4570">132 Stat. 4570</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/119/21/tI/s10601/e">Pub. L. 119–21, title I, § 10601(e)</ref>, <date date="2025-07-04">July 4, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/108">139 Stat. 108</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id78e34d9d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id78e34d9e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id78e34d9f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2025—<ref href="/us/pl/119/21">Pub. L. 119–21</ref> substituted “$150,000,000 for fiscal year 2026 and each fiscal year thereafter, to remain available until expended” for “$50,000,000 for fiscal year 2019 and each fiscal year thereafter”.</p>
</note>
